<h3>How to enable unicode <script>document.write(lang1)</script> conversion in your web pages</h3>
<p>To make a textbox or a textarea field in your web page form enabled with unicode <script>document.write(lang1)</script> typing is very simple. Follow the steps instructions given below. 
<br><br>
1) Include the following code in the &lt;HEAD&gt; section of the webpage:<br>

<div class="codediv">
&lt;SCRIPT language=JavaScript src="http://www.higopi.com/script/ucedit/common.js"&gt;&lt;/SCRIPT&gt;<br>
&lt;SCRIPT language=JavaScript src="http://www.higopi.com/script/ucedit/<script>document.write(lang)</script>.js"&gt;&lt;/SCRIPT&gt;<br>

</div><br>
2) In the &lt;TEXTAREA&gt; or &lt;INPUT TYPE="TEXT"&gt; you want to enable <script>document.write(lang1)</script> unicode conversion, include the following:<br>

<div class="codediv">
&lt;form name="post" method="post"&gt;<br>
&lt;textarea name="comment" charset="utf-8" <span class=redbold>onKeyDown="toggleKBMode(event)" onKeyPress="javascript:convertThis(event)"</span>&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;<br>

&lt;/form&gt;</div><br>
3) You can have radio buttons for shifting between "Phonetic" and "<script>document.write(lang1)</script> Typewriter" layouts as follows:<br>
<div class="codediv">
&lt;input type=radio name=keybrd <span class=redbold>value=roman onclick="toggleKBMode(event,this)"</span> checked&gt;<br>

Phonetic &lt;br&gt;<br>
&lt;input type=radio name=keybrd <span class=redbold>value=typewriter onclick="toggleKBMode(event,this)"</span>&gt;<br>

<script>document.write(lang1); if(lang != "tamil") document.write(" Inscript") </script> Typewriter&lt;br&gt;
<script>if(lang == "tamil")
{
document.write('<br>&lt;input type=radio name=keybrd <span class=redbold>value=tamil99 onclick="toggleKBMode(event,this)"</span>&gt; Tamil 99 &lt;br&gt;<br>');
document.write('<br>&lt;input type=radio name=keybrd <span class=redbold>value=bamini onclick="toggleKBMode(event,this)"</span>&gt; Bamini &lt;br&gt;<br>');
document.write('<br>&lt;input type=radio name=keybrd <span class=redbold>value=vaanavil onclick="toggleKBMode(event,this)"</span>&gt; Vaanavil &lt;br&gt;<br>');
document.write('<br>&lt;input type=radio name=keybrd <span class=redbold>value=modular onclick="toggleKBMode(event,this)"</span>&gt; Modular &lt;br&gt;<br>');
}
</script>
<script>if(lang == "telugu")
document.write('<br>&lt;input type=radio name=keybrd <span class=redbold>value=applete onclick="toggleKBMode(event,this)"</span>&gt; Telugu Apple Typewriter&lt;br&gt;<br>');
</script>
</div><br>

4) You can enable the Show Keymap as follows:<br>
<div class="codediv">
&lt;input type=checkbox <span class=redbold>onclick="showMap(this)"</span>&gt;&nbsp;Show Keymap&lt;br&gt;
</div><br>

5) You can enable the Online Keymap Help as follows:<br>
<div class="codediv">
&lt;input type=checkbox <span class=redbold>onclick="showHelp(this)" checked="true"</span>&gt;&nbsp;Online Keymap Help&lt;br&gt;

</div><br>
